Recruitment Policies<br>
<br>
(The link to the application is at the bottom of the page - 
please take the time to read this before submitting your form.)<p></p>

<p align="left">Question: 
&quot;What do I get out of it?&quot;</p>

<p align="left">Answer: 
The benefits you receive come from the other members 
of the Dynasty.</p>

<blockquote>

<p align="left">* Protection<br>
*
Companionship<br>
*
Friendship<br>
*
Trust<br>
*
Honesty<br>
*
Knowledge</p>

</blockquote>

<p align="left">These are just a few of the benefits 
you will receive. Many others are just as important, but there are too many to 
name. Suffice it to say, we are a family.&nbsp; We help those who help others.&nbsp; 
You will find that the more help you offer, the more likely you will find others 
in the Dynasty helping you.</p>

<p align="left">Do not expect to be given a fixed 
amount of money or items when requested, you will be given what can be spared by 
your friends. This generosity is a two way street and you will be called upon to 
provide when you are able as well.</p>

<p align="left">Do not expect to be power leveled.</p>
<p align="left">Do not expect to get level 50+ items 
at level 15.</p>
<p align="left">Do not expect free handouts with out 
putting any effort into making yourself part of this family.<br>
&nbsp;</p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="border-left-width: 1; border-right-width: 1; border-top-style: solid; border-top-width: 1; border-bottom-width: 1">
<p align="left"><br>
Question: 
&quot;What will I have to do as an applicant?&quot;</p>
<p align="left">Answer: 
The following criteria must be met in order to be considered for membership in 
into The Dragon Dynasty.</p>
<blockquote>
  <p align="left">* 
  Obtain Sponsorship from two current and active guild members<br>
  * Submit an application for membership<br>
  * Login to The <a href="http://pub3.ezboard.com/bthedynastyforum">Dynasty Forum</a> and make your self known to the Membership<br>
  * Learn the Code of Honor and adhere to it.<br>
  * Introduce yourself to all available members of the Dynasty. One way 
  to do this is to take advantage of<br>
  &nbsp; our <a style="background-color: #000000" href="http://server5.ezboard.com/bthedynastyforum" target="_blank">message board system</a>. You must register with us in order to post.<br>
  * Get to know us. The guild is about friendship 
  and adventure. You will find that we are actually 
  a nice<br>
  &nbsp;&nbsp; bunch of folks.<br>
  * Have fun! The game should be about having fun.</p>
</blockquote>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="border-left-width: 1; border-right-width: 1; border-top-style: solid; border-top-width: 1; border-bottom-width: 1">
<p align="left"><br>
Sponsorship and 
What It Means</p>
<blockquote>
  <p align="left">Any &quot;active&quot; Dynasty member in good standing
  can sponsor someone for membership into the guild.<br>
  When considering sponsorship, The Council will evaluate potential guild
  members based on the following:</p>
    <p align="left">* How do you conduct
    yourself when playing your character?<br>
    * Can you make a
    contribution to our guild as a member?<br>
    * Are you going to give
    our guild a good or bad name?<br>
    * How well do you do in
    grouping situations?<br>
    * How well do you do in
    solo situations?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Sponsoring
a Member</p>
<blockquote>
  <p>Please remember that all members represent The Dynasty through deeds and
  actions. The person sponsored today will reflect back on the guild as a whole.</p>
  <p>Please take care when offering to sponsor someone. </p>
  <p>Please also keep in mind the following when evaluating someone for
  membership into The Dragon Dynasty:</p>
   
    <p>* Maturity<br>
    * Helpfulness<br>
    * Dependability<br>
    * Loyalty</p>
             
  <p>Also.. .please post a message on the message board
  stating your sponsorship. It is also your duty to see that your recruit gets
  the web address and makes themselves known on the message boards as well.</p>
</blockquote>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="border-left-width: 1; border-right-width: 1; border-top-style: solid; border-top-width: 1; border-bottom-width: 1">
<p align="left"><br>
In order to become a full member you 
have to work at it everyday and when finally accepted, then the true work will 
begin. Every member of the Dynasty contributes to the overall health of the 
guild. Only through our combined work can the Dynasty truly prosper for all.&nbsp; 
The guild is not only about loot and adventure. It is about loyalty, friendship 
and trust.&nbsp; These are the true rewards.</p>
<p>The Dragon Dynasty has a very strong moral code. We only allow entrance to
those who share similar beliefs and respect the meaning behind the words Honor, Honesty&amp; Friendship.</p>
<p>The Dragon Dynasty believes that membership is a privilege and honor. By submitting your
application you agree to acknowledge and follow the Code
of Honor. You also agree to take an active and productive role in the 
guild. Only one character is considered
your &quot;main&quot; character, however, your alternate 
characters 
are welcome on guild chat as long as you identify yourself ahead of time. You also agree to keep the guild updated 
with your Email address or other means of communication. This will not be made 
public.</p>
<p>At this time, if you have met all the criteria and have your
sponsors, please click on the following link:</p>
<p align="center">
<a href="data/email/recruit_form.asp"><font size="2" color="#FF0000">RECRUIT 
APPLICATION</font></a></p>
